Cannot stop thinking about Gene Wolfe saying us seeing space rockets as "phallic" is our delusion; and actually they represent the mechanical equivalent of an elongated single-cell microorganism. The things one sees under a microscope, if he looks at a drop of muddy gutter water.

Another idea of his is that any intelligent life we could find in space would be us, man, again. Simply having forgotten we were there already. Like Greek sculptors seeing only themselves wherever they looked in nature or Europeans hearing Native American legends about white gods
